.Im MicroEmacs command|insert
.ds C0 "(\fB\*(tA\fR)\ \&
.so me.tni
.TH tab 2
.XI tab \- "\*(C0Handle the tab key"
.SH NAME
tab \- Handle the tab key
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
\fBtab\fR \*(C0
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tab
manages the \fCtab\fR key, typically  inserts \fIn\fR tabs. The effect of the
command is determined by:
.IP \fB$buffer-indent\fR
If
.Ht $buffer-indent 5 ,
is  non-zero  then  the  effect  of  tab  is  defined  by the  setting  of bit
\fC0x1000\fR of variable
.Ht $system 5 ,
typically it resets the current line indentation or inserts a tab.
.IP \fBcmode\fR
If cmode is  enabled  then the effect of tab is defined by the  setting of bit
\fC0x1000\fR of variable
.Ht $system 5 ,
typically it resets the current line indentation or inserts a tab.
.IP \fBtab\fR
If a tab is to be inserted  and this mode is enabled then multiple  spaces are
used instead of tab characters, see
.Ht tab 2m
mode.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
